HEADWORD: Flyaway
<hw>Fly"a*way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Disposed to fly
away; flighty; unrestrained; light and free; -- used of both persons and
things.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A flyaway person or
thing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Truth is such a <xex>flyaway</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Emerson.</au></rj></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

